channel.title: Help with my Hard-Drive space on my Vista laptop!
channel.description:
Alright, well. I have to go back to my stupid Windows Vista Laptop because of my stupid little cousin spilling a cup of water on my Windows XP with all my programs like VB, C#, C++, VS, ETC.... But well, this Vista has 27.9 GB in all. Now the most I can really get is about 6 GB :l I have already went to cmd and typed "Compcln.exe" to clean how some of the winsxs file or whatever. I have done cleaned up lots of crap I don't need. I deleted the "Sun" Folder. I downloaded CCleaner to clean up some of the temps, cache, cookies, ETC... Any help guys?
I'll rep++ if you help me a lot<3 :]

item.title: Help with my Hard-Drive space on my Vista laptop!
item.dc:creator: @bowserjr2 Bowser jr
item.description:
@bowserjr2 wrote:

Demand money back from your little cousin, you can’t let him get away with destroying your computer.

[quote=“ictbguud, post:7, topic:455158”]This is a old kind of laptop bro… Now go away if you are just going to talk and not help…

Also, Fridder. I have like no more programs I can delete. Just ones I need like to make Windows Funtion :(.

And I can’t spend NONE of my money… I gotta pay the light bill… Fking $460, Truck payment is $760…

I really can’t spend money atm… :l[/quote]
Are you sure you are only 14?

OK, reinstall Vista. You should then have 12.0 GB used.
hiberfil.sys and pagefile.sys take up about 6.28 GB. Deactivate hibernation and reduce the allowed size of the page file. You would then have over 20 GB free to use.
